The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 29 August is 2,942 (340.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 25 August, there were 61 new confirmed cases (7.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 18 August, there were 38 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 61% (23 extra cases).
